				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: One of my favorite<a name="4277"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 12 03 1:06 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Actually, I thought of another use for it, raid wipe time!
<br />

<br />
Ok, my guild regularly wipes at least once on raids, mainly because we are still growing and testing the waters on the higher raid spots with minimal experience there.
<br />

<br />
Here's my idea. Not sure if it will work but here it goes:
<br />

<br />
The raid party is doomed and a wipe is evident.  The raid leader calls for the epic cleric to camp.  If she's smart, she DAs herself and either sits and camps or simply /q's.
<br />

<br />
At that point she has 18 of her 30 seconds taken care of, the last part she's vunerable.  If I step near her and crank this song up say, 15 seconds into her camping, that clears the remainder of her camp out with my DA.
<br />

<br />
I'm thinking of this scenario when it is hopeless to run as you will just have corpses farther from camp.
<br />

<br />
In regular group situations, I can see that this would be awesome, there is rarely a time when you can't either get to zone or far enough away (with selos hit right before this song is played) to evac or maybe even camp. Hehe almost as good as the mythical FD song! ROFL
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
