				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree with Sinfonan, but I rarely use this song. Part of it is the 3 min prep time to cast and the value of the slot it takes.
<br />

<br />
Times when I do:
<br />
1. Escourting lower-hp classes through ME to UP/AR (how many times to they die within inches of UP?) Just hit this song as you near the entrance to the ZO and the mobs just dance around you w/out hitting.
<br />

<br />
2. On raids when I suspect a possible wipe... I swap it out for another toon 3 min before we get to a wipe spot and let the cleric know to DA first and I'll save her butt the last 1/2 of the camp. Be sure your tanks click this off so they can melee the other mobs so other casters can camp out.
<br />

<br />
3. Bardapault. Have a raid stuck in Hate/Fear without a wizard to TL ya? And you only have 1 druid? Just bardapalt your raid out. Think about it a sec and you'll get it. Be advised of your timing for this song... missing it will strand your raid at Inny's feet with a full spawn below and noone to gate them.
<br />

<br />
Anyone have any other creative uses?</span></td>
